483
00:18:34,197 --> 00:18:37,655
with a sort of
throwback, ironic twist.

484
00:18:37,738 --> 00:18:39,197
And we're in charge
of defending

485
00:18:39,280 --> 00:18:42,030
what's known
as the Sacred Timeline.

486
00:18:42,113 --> 00:18:45,280
Holy fuck. That is a shit-ton
of exposition for a threequel.

487
00:18:45,363 --> 00:18:47,280
Is this because
I used Cable's time machine?

488
00:18:47,363 --> 00:18:49,072
Brought a couple of people
back to life,

489
00:18:49,155 --> 00:18:50,197
then I destroyed it.

490
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:51,738
- That was a long time ago.
- Yes,

491
00:18:51,822 --> 00:18:54,447
we're aware of your abuse
of your timeline.

492
00:18:54,530 --> 00:18:56,780
[chuckles] And you were
so abusive of it.

493
00:18:57,238 --> 00:18:59,530
Uh, no, it has nothing
to do with that.

494
00:18:59,613 --> 00:19:00,697
Walk with me.

495
00:19:02,905 --> 00:19:04,905
[♪ mysterious music playing]

496
00:19:06,655 --> 00:19:09,280
I brought you here,
Mr. Wilson, to tell you

497
00:19:09,363 --> 00:19:10,780
that you're special.

498
00:19:11,530 --> 00:19:14,405
In fact, you've been chosen
for a higher purpose,

499
00:19:14,488 --> 00:19:16,280
a purpose unclear even to me.

500
00:19:16,697 --> 00:19:18,822
But one that could

501
00:19:18,905 --> 00:19:21,905
save the entire
Sacred Timeline

502
00:19:21,988 --> 00:19:24,572
from a possibly grisly fate
sometime in the future,

503
00:19:24,655 --> 00:19:27,155
which may very well
need to be...

504
00:19:27,238 --> 00:19:28,988
avenged.

505
00:19:29,072 --> 00:19:30,697
This Sacred Timeline,

506
00:19:31,780 --> 00:19:33,697
I assume I'm going to marvel

507
00:19:34,197 --> 00:19:35,238
at how

508
00:19:35,905 --> 00:19:37,655
cinematic it feels?

509
00:19:37,738 --> 00:19:39,780
Gratuitous cameos,

510
00:19:39,863 --> 00:19:41,780
indiscriminate use of
Variants, the whole package?

511
00:19:41,863 --> 00:19:43,822
Well, you tell me.

512
00:19:43,905 --> 00:19:44,905
[device beeps]

513
00:19:47,697 --> 00:19:49,697
[♪ heroic music playing]

514
00:19:50,863 --> 00:19:51,863
Cap!

515
00:19:58,988 --> 00:20:01,572
You are no longer lost, Wade.

516
00:20:01,655 --> 00:20:04,113
You can be a hero
among heroes.

517
00:20:04,655 --> 00:20:06,822
We've been surveilling you
for quite a while.

518
00:20:06,905 --> 00:20:09,738
- Subway station.
- A TVA outpost, yes.

519
00:20:10,947 --> 00:20:12,072
- And what is that?
- Hmm?

520
00:20:15,113 --> 00:20:16,488
Is that me? Is that Thor?

521
00:20:17,988 --> 00:20:19,780
- Is he crying?
- Uh, let's not

522
00:20:19,863 --> 00:20:21,238
- get ahead of ourselves.
- [gasps]

523
00:20:21,322 --> 00:20:22,613
That happens
in the distant future.

524
00:20:22,697 --> 00:20:24,488
Why is Thor crying?
Quick! Tell me.

525
00:20:24,572 --> 00:20:26,113
Do not speak to her.
Stop that. Eyes on me.

526
00:20:26,197 --> 00:20:28,405
I brought you here
to offer you an opportunity.

527
00:20:28,488 --> 00:20:30,405
The opportunity
you sought years ago,

528
00:20:30,488 --> 00:20:31,905
but for which
you were not ready.

529
00:20:31,988 --> 00:20:33,613
We believe you're ready now.

530
00:20:33,697 --> 00:20:35,738
Ready for a chance
to leave your timeline

531
00:20:35,822 --> 00:20:38,155
and join the greatest
universe of all.

532
00:20:38,238 --> 00:20:39,947
I am about to give you the
thing you've always wanted.

533
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:41,655
Oh, I smell
what you're steppin' in.

534
00:20:41,738 --> 00:20:43,030
The power
in the Marvel Universe

535
00:20:43,113 --> 00:20:44,155
is about to change forever.

536
00:20:46,530 --> 00:20:48,155
I am the Messiah...

537
00:20:48,238 --> 00:20:49,905
[♪ heavenly music building]

538
00:20:49,988 --> 00:20:52,155
I am...

539
00:20:53,613 --> 00:20:54,988
- [♪ music stops]
- ...Marvel Jesus.

540
00:20:56,405 --> 00:20:57,863
Can you excuse me
for just a moment?

541
00:20:57,947 --> 00:20:59,322
I'm just gonna go over here.

542
00:21:02,530 --> 00:21:03,988
Suck it, Fox!

543
00:21:04,072 --> 00:21:05,363
I'm going to Disneyland.

544
00:21:05,447 --> 00:21:06,780
[grunts] Get fucked!

545
00:21:10,405 --> 00:21:11,405
Where do I sign?

546
00:21:11,488 --> 00:21:12,572
Oh, there's no need
for paperwork.

547
00:21:12,655 --> 00:21:14,822
Good. Not to brag,
but I do not read.

548
00:21:14,905 --> 00:21:15,905
[chuckles] Oh.

549
00:21:15,988 --> 00:21:17,947
There is one thing
I will need, though.

550
00:21:20,697 --> 00:21:22,072
[♪ rousing music playing]

551
00:21:22,155 --> 00:21:24,613
[laughs] Oh, fuck off!

552
00:21:24,697 --> 00:21:26,655
Adorn me, Beardo.

553
00:21:41,697 --> 00:21:43,238
- [squeaks]
- [elevator dings]

554
00:21:45,113 --> 00:21:47,155
[♪ hip-hop music plays, Fergie
ft. Ludacris "Glamorous"]

555
00:21:47,238 --> 00:21:48,238
Fuckin' A!

556
00:21:48,697 --> 00:21:51,072
Uhh! It's perfect! FYI,

557
00:21:51,155 --> 00:21:54,197
your tailor is a predator,
but I love it. Snug.

558
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:55,405
No camel toe.

559
00:21:55,488 --> 00:21:58,655
New car smell
and adamantium katanas?

560
00:21:59,030 --> 00:22:00,488
You shouldn't have.

561
00:22:00,822 --> 00:22:02,905
Go ahead. Take it in.

562
00:22:02,988 --> 00:22:05,613
And yes, your underwear
is getting tighter.

563
00:22:05,697 --> 00:22:07,363
That guy knows
what I'm talking about.

564
00:22:07,447 --> 00:22:09,030
His clothes says
middle management,

565
00:22:09,113 --> 00:22:11,655
but his eyes say
fuck-y fuck-y.

566
00:22:11,738 --> 00:22:13,613
Yes. You look very nice.

567
00:22:13,697 --> 00:22:14,697
[Deadpool] "Nice"?

568
00:22:14,780 --> 00:22:16,822
Your buddy here is ready
to throw it all away for me.

569
00:22:16,905 --> 00:22:18,197
- You callin' your wife?
- HR.

570
00:22:18,280 --> 00:22:19,530
[Deadpool] Does your wife
work in HR?

571
00:22:19,613 --> 00:22:21,697
[Mr. Paradox] I'm really glad
you're taking this so well.

572
00:22:22,072 --> 00:22:23,905
[Deadpool]
Oh, I'm taking it well.

573
00:22:23,988 --> 00:22:26,363
I have never had a problem
traveling for work.

574
00:22:26,447 --> 00:22:28,280
That said,
we should talk vacation days.

575
00:22:28,655 --> 00:22:31,113
I'm more of a one-week-on-
one-week-off kind of guy.

576
00:22:31,197 --> 00:22:32,655
I think it's what they do
in Denmark.

577
00:22:32,738 --> 00:22:34,447
You know, you'll never see
a Danish flag on the moon,

578
00:22:34,530 --> 00:22:36,405
but [chuckles]
goddamn it, they're happy.

579
00:22:36,488 --> 00:22:39,072
Now, let's power up your
little Amazon Fire phone there

580
00:22:39,155 --> 00:22:40,697
and zip me back home

581
00:22:40,780 --> 00:22:42,447
so I can let my friends know
that they've been upgraded

582
00:22:42,530 --> 00:22:43,780
to disciples.

583
00:22:43,863 --> 00:22:46,863
Yeah. I don't think you...
quite understand.

584
00:22:46,947 --> 00:22:49,530
Um, you will not be returning
to your home

585
00:22:49,613 --> 00:22:51,905
because there will be
no home to return to.

586
00:22:51,988 --> 00:22:52,988
Come again?

587
00:22:53,072 --> 00:22:54,113
This time in my ears.

588
00:22:56,405 --> 00:22:57,405
[device beeps]

589
00:22:58,488 --> 00:23:01,405
This is your universe,
Mr. Wilson.

590
00:23:02,030 --> 00:23:03,363
That

591
00:23:03,447 --> 00:23:05,322
is what happens
when a universe

592
00:23:05,405 --> 00:23:07,613
loses their Anchor Being.

593
00:23:07,697 --> 00:23:09,863
See how it decays
from the inside?

594
00:23:09,947 --> 00:23:12,697
