- What's an Anchor Being?

595
00:23:12,780 --> 00:23:14,988
An Anchor Being is an entity
of such vital importance

596
00:23:15,072 --> 00:23:16,072
that when they die,

597
00:23:16,155 --> 00:23:19,738
their whole world slowly
withers out of existence.

598
00:23:19,822 --> 00:23:22,572
You've just won the lottery
because I didn't die.

599
00:23:22,655 --> 00:23:24,405
It was just a little midlife
crisis. I'm better now.

600
00:23:24,488 --> 00:23:26,697
Oh, no, no, no. [laughing]

601
00:23:28,905 --> 00:23:30,655
[Deadpool laughs along]

602
00:23:30,738 --> 00:23:33,447
- Oh, my God.
- Oh, I love to laugh.

603
00:23:33,530 --> 00:23:36,113
Can you imagine
if you were the Anchor Being?

604
00:23:36,197 --> 00:23:38,280
- [Deadpool, dully] Yeah.
- [laughs] Oh!

605
00:23:38,363 --> 00:23:40,780
- Yeah.
- No, it isn't you, Mr. Wilson.

606
00:23:41,613 --> 00:23:42,905
Your Anchor Being died

607
00:23:42,988 --> 00:23:45,905
in an act
of self-sacrifice so epic

608
00:23:46,322 --> 00:23:48,447
that it sent shivers
down the Timeline.

609
00:23:48,822 --> 00:23:51,655
I am referring,
of course, to...

610
00:23:53,072 --> 00:23:56,780
Logan. The Wolverine.

611
00:24:00,322 --> 00:24:02,655
[weakly] <i>Don't be
what they made you.</i>

612
00:24:03,780 --> 00:24:06,238
[♪ sentimental slow rock
music playing]

613
00:24:11,030 --> 00:24:12,697
[crying]

614
00:24:12,780 --> 00:24:15,197
<i>Ah, so this is
what it feels like...</i>

615
00:24:17,030 --> 00:24:18,030
[Deadpool] Logan.

616
00:24:18,947 --> 00:24:19,947
Of course.

617
00:24:20,530 --> 00:24:21,530
Logan.

618
00:24:23,322 --> 00:24:24,363
[Deadpool groans]

619
00:24:24,447 --> 00:24:25,822
[yelling] Logan?

620
00:24:25,905 --> 00:24:27,822
The guy with forks for hands?

621
00:24:27,905 --> 00:24:29,780
- That Wolverine?
- [device beeps]

622
00:24:30,655 --> 00:24:32,363
Yeah, I got it.
You can turn your

623
00:24:32,447 --> 00:24:34,780
retro graphics of death
off now. Make it stop.

624
00:24:34,863 --> 00:24:36,197
We're not doing it,
Mr. Wilson.

625
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:37,322
We certainly can't stop it.

626
00:24:39,655 --> 00:24:40,655
[Deadpool]
How long have we got?

627
00:24:40,738 --> 00:24:43,280
In most cases,
couple thousand years.

628
00:24:43,363 --> 00:24:44,655
- Well, sweet.
- Well, most cases

629
00:24:44,738 --> 00:24:46,488
aren't fast enough.
Not for me.

630
00:24:47,072 --> 00:24:48,155
[Deadpool]
What does that mean?

631
00:24:48,238 --> 00:24:50,405
It means
that I have been tasked

632
00:24:50,488 --> 00:24:52,738
with overseeing
the end of your universe.

633
00:24:52,822 --> 00:24:53,822
And regardless of what

634
00:24:53,905 --> 00:24:55,613
the pencil pushers upstairs
would prefer,

635
00:24:55,697 --> 00:24:56,822
I will not

636
00:24:57,280 --> 00:25:00,655
waste my life watching it die
slowly of natural causes.

637
00:25:00,738 --> 00:25:02,863
We used to just prune
these things. Simple.

638
00:25:02,947 --> 00:25:04,863
Elegant. Efficient.
But I'm told the TVA

639
00:25:04,947 --> 00:25:07,280
doesn't like to do that
anymore. Well, I do.

640
00:25:07,363 --> 00:25:09,072
And no matter what
my so-called superiors say,

641
00:25:09,155 --> 00:25:11,613
the multiverse does not
need a babysitter.

642
00:25:11,697 --> 00:25:13,488
We need a mercy killer.

643
00:25:13,572 --> 00:25:15,155
And in this instance,

644
00:25:15,238 --> 00:25:18,322
I am the mercy killer. Ha!

645
00:25:19,697 --> 00:25:20,697
[chuckles]

646
00:25:21,780 --> 00:25:22,780
[device beeps]

647
00:25:22,863 --> 00:25:24,738
[Deadpool] What in
the MacGuffin is that?

648
00:25:24,822 --> 00:25:26,947
[Mr. Paradox] That's
a Time Ripper, Mr. Wilson.

649
00:25:27,030 --> 00:25:28,780
An accelerant.

650
00:25:28,863 --> 00:25:31,447
Once completed,
it will allow me to destroy

651
00:25:31,530 --> 00:25:33,530
the spacetime matrix
of your universe.

652
00:25:33,613 --> 00:25:35,697
You see, I don't want
to work for the TVA.

653
00:25:35,780 --> 00:25:37,822
I want to be the TVA.

654
00:25:37,905 --> 00:25:40,530
And the first step involves
showing this organization

655
00:25:40,613 --> 00:25:42,405
how much more efficient
it can become.

656
00:25:42,488 --> 00:25:44,238
To wit, I will be
giving your universe

657
00:25:44,322 --> 00:25:46,947
a swift and compassionate end.

658
00:25:47,030 --> 00:25:48,405
And don't worry, your friends
won't feel a thing.

659
00:25:48,488 --> 00:25:51,030
It'll be over just like this.
"Oh, what's that?" [groans]

660
00:25:51,780 --> 00:25:52,863
Trust me.

661
00:26:05,572 --> 00:26:07,822
You're gonna Old Yeller
my fucking universe?

662
00:26:07,905 --> 00:26:10,113
Mm... In your parlance, yes.

663
00:26:10,197 --> 00:26:11,655
Two in the heart,
one in the head.

664
00:26:11,738 --> 00:26:13,780
Look, Mr. Wilson,
you have two choices.

665
00:26:13,863 --> 00:26:15,197
You can either rejoin
your loved ones

666
00:26:15,280 --> 00:26:17,072
and collectively cease
to exist in,

667
00:26:17,155 --> 00:26:19,405
I'd say, 72 hours. Or...

668
00:26:20,238 --> 00:26:22,863
you join the Sacred Timeline.

669
00:26:22,947 --> 00:26:25,155
And you end your days
of insignificance

670
00:26:25,238 --> 00:26:27,238
and mediocrity.

671
00:26:27,322 --> 00:26:28,447
Wade.

672
00:26:29,072 --> 00:26:30,863
Wade, you can finally,

673
00:26:30,947 --> 00:26:33,363
finally matter.

674
00:26:37,822 --> 00:26:40,363
- [Hulk roars]
- [♪ sentimental music playing]

675
00:26:43,113 --> 00:26:45,238
That's all
I've ever really wanted.

676
00:26:45,322 --> 00:26:46,572
I know.

677
00:26:47,197 --> 00:26:48,197
I know.

678
00:26:49,155 --> 00:26:51,322
And you know I'm...
I'm nothing if not

679
00:26:51,405 --> 00:26:52,655
morally flexible. [chuckles]

680
00:26:53,197 --> 00:26:54,197
[chuckles]

681
00:26:55,113 --> 00:26:56,113
Yep, yep.

682
00:26:58,405 --> 00:26:59,405
I'll do it.

683
00:26:59,488 --> 00:27:00,488
Wise choice.

684
00:27:00,572 --> 00:27:02,405
The Sacred Timeline's happy
to have you.

685
00:27:02,488 --> 00:27:03,530
[Deadpool] I was actually
talking about finding

686
00:27:03,613 --> 00:27:05,280
the Wolverine and breaking
your fucking nose.

687
00:27:06,238 --> 00:27:07,238
[groans]

688
00:27:08,988 --> 00:27:09,988
[♪ soft rock music plays,
Goo Goo Dolls "Iris"]

689
00:27:10,072 --> 00:27:13,197
<i>♪ And I'd give up forever
to touch you ♪</i>

690
00:27:13,280 --> 00:27:17,030
<i>♪ 'Cause I know
that you feel me somehow ♪</i>

691
00:27:17,113 --> 00:27:18,113
[♪ song stops]

692
00:27:19,113 --> 00:27:21,530
Find him. Find him!

693
00:27:21,613 --> 00:27:23,322
[Deadpool]
<i>And boy, did he ever.</i>

694
00:27:23,405 --> 00:27:24,863
[grunting]

695
00:27:25,238 --> 00:27:26,655
<i>Which brings us back to this.</i>

696
00:27:28,822 --> 00:27:30,780
<i>The desecration
of the sacred corpse.</i>

697
00:27:31,238 --> 00:27:33,780
- [♪ dramatic music playing]
- [yelling and grunting]

698
00:27:35,113 --> 00:27:36,738
- Oh, my God!
- [yells]

699
00:27:37,738 --> 00:27:40,363
Oh! My own fucking arm!

700
00:27:40,822 --> 00:27:41,988
[soldier 1 yells]

701
00:27:42,072 --> 00:27:43,655
- [soldier 1 screams]
- [grunting]

702
00:27:44,072 --> 00:27:45,530
- [soldier 1 screaming]
- Now we're talkin'!

703
00:27:45,613 --> 00:27:46,947
[soldier 1] Not like this!

704
00:27:47,030 --> 00:27:49,197
No, dear God! No!

705
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:51,405
[Deadpool] I'm sorry!
Wolverine-ing is hard!

706
00:27:51,488 --> 00:27:52,697
[soldier 2] Make it stop!

707
00:27:52,780 --> 00:27:53,988
[Deadpool] Mangold tried.

708
00:27:54,072 --> 00:27:55,905
[soldiers screaming]

709
00:27:56,780 --> 00:27:58,822
You sick fuck!

710
00:27:58,905 --> 00:28:00,072
Logan was a hero.

711
00:28:00,405 --> 00:28:01,822
And the only thing
worth a shit

712
00:28:01,905 --> 00:28:03,155
to ever come out of Canada.

713
00:28:03,822 --> 00:28:04,863
[soldier 1 cries out]

714
00:28:05,572 --> 00:28:06,572
[soldier 2 screams]

715
00:28:11,113 --> 00:28:13,322
[Deadpool]
Get my country's name

716
00:28:13,405 --> 00:28:15,405
out of your fuckin' mouth.

717
00:28:16,530 --> 00:28:18,113
And my sword. Give me that.

718
00:28:20,447 --> 00:28:21,488
[exhales]

719
00:28:21,572 --> 00:28:23,863
Oh, I gotta find me
another Logan.

720
00:28:24,405 --> 00:28:25,780
An alive one.

721
00:28:25,863 --> 00:28:28,030
Don't get up, guys.
I'll see myself out.

722
00:28:28,863 --> 00:28:31,280
[♪ synth rock music playing,
"The Power of Love"]

723
00:28:35,530 --> 00:28:36,530
Logan!

724
00:28:40,197 --> 00:28:41,947
I'm gonna need you
to come with me.

725
00:28:43,113 --> 00:28:44,113
Who's asking?

726
00:28:45,113 --> 00:28:46,113
[♪ music stops]

727
00:28:46,197 --> 00:28:48,405
[Deadpool] Oh, look at
this little Hairy Lou Retton.

728
00:28:48,488 --> 00:28:50,072
Did you stick the landing,
little guy?

729
00:28:50,738 --> 00:28:51,738
Yes, you did!

730
00:28:51,822 --> 00:28:53,613
Comic-accurate short king.

731
00:28:53,697 --> 00:28:55,613
Such a cute wittle Wolvie.

732
00:28:55,988 --> 00:28:57,738
Cue the fuckin' montage, baby.

733
00:28:57,822 --> 00:28:59,405
- [♪ synth rock music resumes]
- Ahoy!

734
