[choir]
<i>♪ When you call my name ♪</i>

2599
01:49:53,530 --> 01:49:55,363
<i>♪ It's like a little prayer ♪</i>

2600
01:49:55,447 --> 01:49:57,488
<i>♪ I'm down on my knees ♪</i>

2601
01:49:57,572 --> 01:49:59,822
<i>♪ I want to take you there ♪</i>

2602
01:49:59,905 --> 01:50:03,738
<i>♪ In the midnight hour
I can feel your power ♪</i>

2603
01:50:03,822 --> 01:50:06,822
<i>♪ Just like a prayer
You know I'll take you there ♪</i>

2604
01:50:06,905 --> 01:50:08,030
[grunting]

2605
01:50:08,113 --> 01:50:09,947
<i>♪ Take you there ♪</i>

2606
01:50:10,030 --> 01:50:14,072
<i>♪ Life is a mystery ♪</i>

2607
01:50:14,155 --> 01:50:16,988
<i>♪ Everyone must stand alone ♪</i>

2608
01:50:17,072 --> 01:50:18,947
[straining]

2609
01:50:19,030 --> 01:50:22,572
<i>- ♪ I hear you call my name ♪</i>
- [grunting]

2610
01:50:22,655 --> 01:50:24,405
<i>- ♪ And it feels like ♪</i>
- [straining]

2611
01:50:27,072 --> 01:50:30,780
<i>- ♪ And it feels like home ♪</i>
- [straining]

2612
01:50:30,863 --> 01:50:32,238
[rumbling]

2613
01:50:38,988 --> 01:50:40,488
[yelling]

2614
01:50:41,030 --> 01:50:42,530
[screaming]

2615
01:50:44,613 --> 01:50:45,822
[♪ music fades]

2616
01:50:45,905 --> 01:50:47,238
[Deadpool] <i>The Wolverine.</i>

2617
01:50:48,322 --> 01:50:50,113
<i>He's a hero in my world.</i>

2618
01:50:52,405 --> 01:50:53,530
[Wolverine] <i>Whoever
you think I am,</i>

2619
01:50:53,613 --> 01:50:54,905
<i>you got the wrong guy.</i>

2620
01:50:56,447 --> 01:50:58,197
[Laura] <i>You were always
the wrong guy...</i>

2621
01:50:59,738 --> 01:51:00,738
<i>till you weren't.</i>

2622
01:51:00,822 --> 01:51:03,322
<i>♪ Life is a mystery ♪</i>

2623
01:51:03,405 --> 01:51:04,863
[Mr. Paradox] <i>Wade.</i>

2624
01:51:04,947 --> 01:51:06,905
<i>♪ Everyone must stand alone ♪</i>

2625
01:51:06,988 --> 01:51:11,280
<i>Wade. You can finally,
finally matter.</i>

2626
01:51:11,363 --> 01:51:13,488
<i>♪ I hear you call my name</i> ♪

2627
01:51:13,572 --> 01:51:17,863
♪ <i>And it feels like ♪</i>

2628
01:51:18,780 --> 01:51:22,530
♪ <i>Home ♪</i>

2629
01:51:22,613 --> 01:51:23,947
[straining]

2630
01:51:24,030 --> 01:51:27,030
<i>♪ I hear your voice ♪</i>

2631
01:51:27,113 --> 01:51:28,405
Vanessa.

2632
01:51:28,488 --> 01:51:30,822
<i>♪ It's like an angel sighing ♪</i>

2633
01:51:30,905 --> 01:51:32,322
<i>I wanna see Vanessa.</i>

2634
01:51:32,405 --> 01:51:36,655
<i>♪ I have no choice
I hear your voice ♪</i>

2635
01:51:36,738 --> 01:51:38,947
<i>♪ Feels like flying ♪</i>

2636
01:51:39,030 --> 01:51:43,238
For the first time in my life,
I am proud to wear this suit.

2637
01:51:44,447 --> 01:51:46,113
<i>It means I'm an X-Man.</i>

2638
01:51:48,613 --> 01:51:50,155
I am the X-Man.

2639
01:51:50,238 --> 01:51:52,322
<i>♪ I can feel your power ♪</i>

2640
01:51:52,405 --> 01:51:55,738
<i>♪ Just like a prayer
You know I'll take you there ♪</i>

2641
01:51:55,822 --> 01:51:57,030
[screaming]

2642
01:51:57,113 --> 01:52:00,447
<i>♪ When you call my name
It's like a little prayer ♪</i>

2643
01:52:00,530 --> 01:52:02,863
<i>♪ I'm down on my knees ♪</i>

2644
01:52:02,947 --> 01:52:04,655
[screaming]

2645
01:52:04,738 --> 01:52:08,280
<i>♪ In the midnight hour
I can feel your power ♪</i>

2646
01:52:08,655 --> 01:52:10,280
<i>♪ Just like a prayer</i> ♪

2647
01:52:10,363 --> 01:52:13,988
♪ <i>You know I'll take you,
take you, take you ♪</i>

2648
01:52:16,405 --> 01:52:17,530
[♪ song fades out]

2649
01:52:24,822 --> 01:52:26,822
[♪ solemn music playing]

2650
01:52:34,238 --> 01:52:35,780
[woman] Paradox.

2651
01:52:37,613 --> 01:52:38,780
You've been busy.

2652
01:52:39,197 --> 01:52:40,322
Well, somebody had to be.

2653
01:52:40,405 --> 01:52:42,322
We had some strange readings
from this location.

2654
01:52:42,405 --> 01:52:43,613
You wouldn't know
anything about

2655
01:52:43,697 --> 01:52:45,322
an unsanctioned Time Ripper,
would you?

2656
01:52:46,113 --> 01:52:47,822
Uh, no. No.
I wouldn't know anything

2657
01:52:47,905 --> 01:52:49,447
about an unsanctioned
Time Ripper.

2658
01:52:49,530 --> 01:52:51,113
Maybe you should ask
Cassandra Nova.

2659
01:52:51,197 --> 01:52:52,322
Because I was assured

2660
01:52:52,405 --> 01:52:54,863
that she was safely held
in The Void. But no,

2661
01:52:54,947 --> 01:52:57,197
she was here.
And she fondled my brain.

2662
01:52:57,280 --> 01:52:59,322
- How did you let this happen?
- You weren't involved at all?

2663
01:52:59,405 --> 01:53:01,988
In stopping her, yes!
Yes, I was.

2664
01:53:02,072 --> 01:53:03,697
But not nearly enough.

2665
01:53:03,780 --> 01:53:05,988
Not as much as the men
who went down there after her.

2666
01:53:06,655 --> 01:53:07,738
My men.

2667
01:53:08,488 --> 01:53:09,488
My friends.

2668
01:53:10,905 --> 01:53:11,905
I warned them.

2669
01:53:11,988 --> 01:53:13,697
That they would be completely
obliterated if they went.

2670
01:53:13,780 --> 01:53:15,197
But they went anyway. Like...

2671
01:53:16,988 --> 01:53:18,072
Like heroes.

2672
01:53:18,530 --> 01:53:20,113
[♪ somber music playing]

2673
01:53:20,197 --> 01:53:21,863
Because that's who they were.

2674
01:53:24,738 --> 01:53:26,155
They just did
what they had to do.

2675
01:53:27,572 --> 01:53:29,155
With no concern
for their own safety.

2676
01:53:32,780 --> 01:53:36,155
The fact that we are
all still standing here

2677
01:53:36,238 --> 01:53:38,988
is a testament
to their heroism.

2678
01:53:42,697 --> 01:53:43,947
Anyway, there's nothing
you or I can do

2679
01:53:44,030 --> 01:53:45,072
to bring them back now.

2680
01:53:46,905 --> 01:53:48,738
[Deadpool] He has risen,
baby girl.

2681
01:53:48,822 --> 01:53:49,822
Fuck!

2682
01:53:49,905 --> 01:53:54,488
<i>♪ And I don't want
the world to see me ♪</i>

2683
01:53:54,572 --> 01:53:59,363
<i>♪ 'Cause I don't think
that they'd understand ♪</i>

2684
01:53:59,447 --> 01:54:03,530
<i>♪ When everything's
made to be broken ♪</i>

2685
01:54:03,613 --> 01:54:08,488
<i>♪ I just want you
to know who I am ♪</i>

2686
01:54:09,363 --> 01:54:10,572
[Deadpool]
Found your new Anchor Being.

2687
01:54:10,655 --> 01:54:13,030
And we're doing just fine,
